==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-one-off.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''one-off'''
#{{idiom}} something that is done, created, etc. only [[once]], and often [[quickly]], [[simply]], or [[improvisation]]ally
#:''I'll put together a quick '''one-off''' as a sample so we can taste the recipe.''
#{{idiom}} a version of software that is a minor, incremental change from a previous version; one containing mostly bug fixes rather than new feature implementation. Probably derived from the numbers used to signify software versioning where, for example, version 2.1 software would be a '''one-off''' of version 2.0, but version 3.0 would be a full-featured release and '''not''' a '''one-off'''.
#:''Please quickly verify just the bug fixes as this is a '''one-off'''.''
#{{idiom}} an irreproducible, one-of-a-kind item or model. In episode 13 of the anime series [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghost_in_the_Shell:_S.A.C._2nd_GIG Ghost in the Shell: S.A.C. 2nd GIG] '''one-off''' is used to describe the beautiful, unique, hand-modeled face of cyborg [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hideo_Kuze Hideo Kuze]. Earlier in the show, the same face was called ''one-of-a-kind''. So '''one-off''' seems to be a synonym for ''one-of-a-kind'' and specific to computer technology. Contrast this with definition number one, which connotes more of a working, rough draft rather than a completed work of art; though, in both cases, the idea of just one item is maintained.
#:''Clearly, the artist created a '''one-off''', indicated by the life-like modeling of facial features and exquisite use of rare, high-tech composites.''

===Adjective===
'''one-off'''
#{{idiom}} a term used in software release process to indicate that the product release is a minor, incremental change; one containing mostly bug fixes rather than new feature implementation. Probably derived from software versioning where, for example, version 2.1 software would be a '''one-off''' of version 2.0, but version 3.0 would be a full-featured release and '''not''' a '''one-off'''.
#:''Please quickly verify just the bug fixes as this is a '''one-off''' release.''